parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system components, including the electronic fuel injector pump, fuel separator, and fuel pump, can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump fails to prime
the fuel system leaks fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose Lower Control Arm Ball Joint Attachment Nut
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose lower control arm ball joint attachment nut can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's ball joint attachment nut is loose
the vehicle's steering and suspension are affected
the vehicle's handling is unstable
the vehicle's tires wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly repair the lower control arm ball joint attachment nut during the recall can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle still experiences looseness in the lower control arm ball joint attachment nut after the recall repair
the vehicle's steering and suspension are still affected
the vehicle's handling is still unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to bind up, become twisted, and jam, making it difficult or impossible to use the seat belt properly, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt becomes tangled or twisted when retracting
the seat belt binds up and becomes jammed
the seat belt is difficult to use or put on
the seat belt does not retract properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Pilot Bearing and Throw Out Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the pilot bearing and throw out bearing can cause the clutch to malfunction, leading to difficulty shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting gears
grinding or screeching noises when shifting
clutch pedal feels abnormal
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A transmission leak can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to difficulty shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaking from the transmission
difficulty shifting gears
grinding or screeching noises when shifting
transmission slipping or hesitation
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal bracket bolt can cause the brake pedal to become loose or fall out, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels loose or spongy
the brake pedal falls out
the brake pedal bracket bolt is loose or missing
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.
